# 07.04 Use Cases

## Overview

The Use Cases document defines practical scenarios where cmdOS provides value by transforming user intent into real-world execution.

cmdOS is designed to operate as an AI Execution Operating System that allows users to accomplish tasks through natural language instead of manually operating multiple applications.

Core principle:

User Goal

↓

AI Understanding

↓

Agent Planning

↓

Capability Selection

↓

Execution

↓

Completed Result

---

# 1. Use Case Purpose

The purpose of Use Cases is to demonstrate how cmdOS solves real-world problems across different user groups.

Use cases define:

- User needs
- Execution workflows
- Required capabilities
- Expected outcomes

